reviewText: I didn't start watching until they were in season 9.  I got season 8 downloaded and purchased season 1 on dvd but could never find seasons 2-7.  I have enjoyed seeeing it.  It is much less scripted and interesting.

Finally after years of waiting Cycle 2 & 3 are finally available on DVD!! Cycle 2 & 3 are arguably the best Seasons of Top Model. Im a dedicated Top Model fan and i cant wait to get my hands on a copy!! No release date yet but hopefully soon!! Already pre ordered mine!!! Hopefully there will be extras and commentary but doubtful...im just happy itsbeing released at all!!

All 5 final contestants were worthy winners and all are just stunning.  The Italy segment is THE clssic moment defining ANTM, and while Shandi brought the drama, "innocent" Yoanna provoked the situation.  I was sure Shandi would win, and I would have been fine with that since she was/is aweseome, but Yoanna was my favorite.  To this day, I think sh'es the most beautiful woman to ever appear on ANTM.  This season rocks every step of the way, I've seen it like four times already and will totally buy this when it comes out.

I love America's Next Top Model. I want dvd's for all the cycles. I did not get to see the first 5 cycles so I can't wait until they come out. They are all facinating between their personalities and their transformations. I never knew they did all that they do on the show. Hurry up dvd's.
Love love love America's Next Top Model!!!!
I love this show. It's great junk TV. The only thing I didn't particularly care for was the cheating. I felt that was unnecessary to show.

I never thought I would enjoy a reality show about modeling, however, America's Next Top Model has become a new addiction for me and I am going to watch all 22 cycles.  It's amazing to see the transformation as the young women grow into top models and I was surprised at how difficult it is and what all they have to do and to learn.  The show is informative and fun and I'm now an avid fan!

I have had the fortune or maybe misfortune to see all of ANTM's cycles minus 19 and 20 and I feel that cycle 2 is definitely one of the better ones. It has some memorable characters (Camille, Shandi) and has genuine heartfelt drama like the episode of about the girl who cheated. What's annoying are some of the photo shoots. They are ridiculous i.e. the water tank shoot and in future cycles they get more silly.

This season if America's Next Top Model is still one of the juiciest in my mind and brought some of the coldest, aggressive ladies to the scene. You've got Camille McDonald, who has more self confidence with her signature walk and who is open about the fact she wants to bring down her enemy Yoanna House with a fake friendship. Yoanna is no angek though; when her buddy Shandi Sullivan has too much to drink, she lets her sleep with an Italian stranger and cheat on her boyfriend. Awful but hey now Yoanna is going to be feeling great tomorrow and Shandi is an emotional wreck. April Wilkner gets help from a girl the first episode and then stabs her in the back episose two. Catie Anderson perfected the art of crying at the drop of a hat. Bethany Harrison tells Tyra that the judges need to get over her chest. I mean there is so much crazy, juicy girl drama that this will always be one of my guilty pleasure throwback reality TV shows. This was also before Tyra Banks got too big for her britches and -shocker alert - actually hangs out with the models like a peer not some Wizard of Oz behind a curtain who only appears to make up words like smize and booty tooch. This is real, old school Tyra and I love it.
Entertaining, very entertaining
